{"questionId":"21453","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>w</mi><mo>=</mo><mtext>i</mtext><mi>z</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>w</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>z</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℂ</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi></math> on the Argand diagram can be transformed to point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>w</mi></math> by two transformations.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Describe these two transformations and give the order in which they are applied.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>rotation of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>90</mn><mo>°</mo></math> (anticlockwise, centre at the origin)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>&nbsp;A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for “rotation” and <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for “<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>90</mn><mo>°</mo></math>”.</p>\n<p><br>followed by a translation of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em><br><br><strong>OR</strong><br>translation of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em><br><br>followed by rotation of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>90</mn><mo>°</mo></math> (anticlockwise, centre at the origin)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em><br><br><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for “rotation” and A1 for “<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>90</mn><mo>°</mo></math>”.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"21453","referenceCode":"21M.1.AHL.TZ1.9b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Describe these two transformations and give the order in which they are applied.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.12—Complex numbers introduction","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.13—Polar and Euler form"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}